@startuml State_Alert
title Alert Lifecycle - State Diagram

skinparam state {
    BackgroundColor<<positive>> #90EE90
    BackgroundColor<<neutral>> #E8E8E8
}

[*] --> Created

Created : Alert generated by\nmonitoring rule
Created --> Delivered : notificationSent\n/ record channels

Delivered : Alert delivered via\npush/email/SMS/in-app
Delivered --> Read : userOpened\n/ record readAt
Delivered --> Expired <<neutral>> : ttlExceeded\n[not read within 30 days]

Read : User has seen the alert
Read --> ActionTaken <<positive>> : userActed\n(cancel, negotiate, dismiss charge)
Read --> Dismissed <<neutral>> : userDismissed\n/ record reason
Read --> Expired <<neutral>> : ttlExceeded\n[no action within 30 days]

ActionTaken <<positive>> : User took recommended\nor alternative action
ActionTaken --> [*]

Dismissed <<neutral>> : User explicitly\ndismissed the alert
Dismissed --> [*]

Expired <<neutral>> : Alert expired without\nuser interaction
Expired --> [*]

note right of Created
  Alerts are created by:
  - PriceChangeDetector
  - NewChargeDetector
  - TrialExpirationTracker
  - RenewalDateTracker
  - MonthlyReportGenerator
end note

note right of ActionTaken
  Actions feed back into
  Features 03-05:
  cancellation, negotiation,
  or plan switch
end note

@enduml
